<font color="yellow">And grandma, Joo-ri didn't bewitch me. I was the one who begged her to date me!</font>

205
00:13:29,181 --> 00:13:31,301
<font color="yellow">I was the first one to tell her that I like her and</font>

206
00:13:31,327 --> 00:13:33,283
<font color="yellow">I was the first one to tell her that I love her!</font>

207
00:13:33,627 --> 00:13:35,796
<font color="yellow">Joo-ri's parents were against us, but I finally</font>

208
00:13:35,821 --> 00:13:37,673
<font color="yellow">got permission after I knelt before them!</font>

209
00:13:38,470 --> 00:13:39,642
<font color="yellow">What did you just say?</font>

210
00:13:39,667 --> 00:13:41,407
<font color="yellow">Die. You should just die instead!</font>

211
00:13:41,432 --> 00:13:44,830
<font color="yellow">Mom!</font>

212
00:13:49,142 --> 00:13:50,548
<font color="yellow">Use your words!</font>

213
00:13:50,573 --> 00:13:51,892
<font color="yellow">Is it a crime to love someone?</font>

214
00:13:54,017 --> 00:13:57,579
<font color="yellow">-What did I do so wrong? -Grandma!</font>

215
00:14:00,939 --> 00:14:02,594
<font color="yellow">Lee Jang-soo, be quiet, will you?</font>

216
00:14:03,416 --> 00:14:05,470
<font color="yellow">Joo-ri is such a kind woman!</font>

217
00:14:06,048 --> 00:14:08,650
<font color="yellow">Is it a crime to love someone?</font>

218
00:14:08,869 --> 00:14:12,226
<font color="yellow">You don't deserve to talk back to me! What are you, a little kid?</font>

219
00:14:14,259 --> 00:14:16,393
<font color="yellow">Jang-go, do you know about love?</font>

220
00:14:17,017 --> 00:14:18,212
<font color="yellow">Do you know about love?</font>

221
00:14:18,759 --> 00:14:20,110
<font color="yellow">You don't know anything.</font>

222
00:14:25,642 --> 00:14:28,277
<font color="yellow">There's no solution for you.</font>

223
00:14:29,345 --> 00:14:32,891
<font color="yellow">If you're going to curse someone, you should curse me! Why curse my nice Joo-ri?</font>

224
00:14:33,002 --> 00:14:34,672
<font color="yellow">How can he become so crazy?</font>

225
00:14:35,447 --> 00:14:37,442
<font color="yellow">Shouldn't we take him to the hospital?</font>

226
00:14:39,212 --> 00:14:42,915
<font color="yellow">This is all your fault!</font>

227
00:14:43,533 --> 00:14:44,533
<font color="yellow">Pardon?</font>

228
00:14:44,690 --> 00:14:47,099
<font color="yellow">Ever since Jang-soo was little, you would only take</font>

229
00:14:47,124 --> 00:14:49,486
<font color="yellow">care of Jang-go and leave Jang-soo out in the dust.</font>

230
00:14:50,050 --> 00:14:55,416
<font color="yellow">Because of the lack of affection, he fell for an old woman!</font>

231
00:14:56,628 --> 00:14:59,649
<font color="yellow">Mom, stop it. Geum-sil is upset enough already.</font>

232
00:15:00,515 --> 00:15:01,924
<font color="yellow">Aren't I telling the truth?</font>

233
00:15:02,127 --> 00:15:05,963
<font color="yellow">Because you stopped Jang-soo from becoming an actor,</font>

234
00:15:06,620 --> 00:15:14,602
<font color="yellow">he fell for that old woman who encouraged him on!</font>

235
00:15:15,112 --> 00:15:19,805
<font color="yellow">Mother, you can't say that just because he isn't your son.</font>

236
00:15:20,050 --> 00:15:23,250
<font color="yellow">If he was your son, would you have allowed him to become a stage actor?</font>

237
00:15:23,275 --> 00:15:25,106
<font color="yellow">He doesn't make proper money from that, and</font>

238
00:15:25,131 --> 00:15:27,003
<font color="yellow">all he does is stick posters on street lamps!</font>

239
00:15:27,028 --> 00:15:28,891
<font color="yellow">What? Jang-soo is your son?</font>

240
00:15:29,414 --> 00:15:32,242
<font color="yellow">Jang-soo is my son. My son.</font>

241
00:15:32,518 --> 00:15:38,777
<font color="yellow">He's my son who I raised in my arms while you left him behind to do business!</font>

242
00:15:39,214 --> 00:15:40,406
<font color="yellow">What are you talking about?</font>

243
00:15:41,039 --> 00:15:42,039
<font color="yellow">Fine.</font>

244
00:15:42,846 --> 00:15:45,573
<font color="yellow">Jang-soo is not my son anymore. He's your son,</font>

245
00:15:45,978 --> 00:15:49,735
<font color="yellow">so you can take him out of this house and let him do whatever he wants.</font>

246
00:15:49,760 --> 00:15:53,316
<font color="yellow">He can become a stage actor or get married to that divorcee with children.</font>

247
00:15:53,341 --> 00:15:57,526
<font color="yellow">What did you say? Are you telling me to leave this house?</font>

248
00:15:57,558 --> 00:16:02,172
<font color="yellow">-Mom! That's not what she means! Go to your room!-You!</font>

249
00:16:02,197 --> 00:16:07,168
<font color="yellow">My son bought this house with money he worked hard to make!</font>

250
00:16:07,193 --> 00:16:10,988
<font color="yellow">Who are you to tell me to leave this house!</font>

251
00:16:11,011 --> 00:16:15,873
<font color="yellow">-How dare you tell me to leave! -What's wrong with you?</font>

252
00:16:30,846 --> 00:16:32,438
<font color="yellow">Mommy, hurry up!</font>

253
00:16:32,464 --> 00:16:33,464
<font color="yellow">Okay!</font>

254
00:16:40,026 --> 00:16:41,357
<font color="yellow">It's hot, so be careful.</font>

255
00:16:42,026 --> 00:16:43,026
<font color="yellow">Here you go.</font>

256
00:16:47,815 --> 00:16:49,704
<font color="yellow">There you go! Here.</font>

257
00:16:50,893 --> 00:16:52,226
<font color="yellow">This is okay, right?</font>

258
00:16:52,479 --> 00:16:53,679
<font color="yellow">Yes, it's perfect!</font>

259
00:16:58,768 --> 00:17:01,605
<font color="yellow">Yoo-sung, starting from tomorrow, we're going</font>

260
00:17:01,631 --> 00:17:04,529
<font color="yellow">to live in a house that has a lot of warm water.</font>

261
00:17:04,846 --> 00:17:05,846
<font color="yellow">Really?</font>

262
00:17:05,871 --> 00:17:07,425
<font color="yellow">Close your eyes, or they'll sting.</font>

263
00:17:08,661 --> 00:17:12,507
<font color="yellow">The new house that we're moving into isn't a semi-basement</font>

264
00:17:12,532 --> 00:17:16,443
<font color="yellow">like this one, so there will be plenty of sunshine and wind.</font>

265
00:17:17,123 --> 00:17:18,310
<font color="yellow">Sounds great, right?</font>

266
00:17:18,335 --> 00:17:19,335
<font color="yellow">Yes!</font>

267
00:17:19,360 --> 00:17:20,825
<font color="yellow">You're so cute, Yoo-sung!</font>

268
00:17:52,582 --> 00:17:53,971
<font color="yellow">Why aren't you sleeping?</font>

269
00:18:00,068 --> 00:18:01,754
<font color="yellow">I knew you would be like this.</font>

270
00:18:04,615 --> 00:18:07,057
<font color="yellow">After losing your dad in a car accident,</font>

271
00:18:09,240 --> 00:18:11,506
<font color="yellow">I thought I had lived pretty well.</font>

272
00:18:13,607 --> 00:18:17,997
<font color="yellow">Today he's on my mind a lot.</font>

273
00:18:19,201 --> 00:18:20,838
<font color="yellow">If your dad had been alive,</font>

274
00:18:22,622 --> 00:18:25,365
<font color="yellow">I wonder what he would have said about what happened tonight.</font>

275
00:18:29,099 --> 00:18:31,907
<font color="yellow">You still have me by your side.</font>

276
00:18:33,076 --> 00:18:34,076
<font color="yellow">I know.</font>

277
00:18:35,693 --> 00:18:36,693
<font color="yellow">Mom.</font>

278
00:18:38,404 --> 00:18:40,192
<font color="yellow">Don't worry about Jang-soo too much.</font>

279
00:18:41,357 --> 00:18:43,356
<font color="yellow">After a few days pass, I'll talk to him about it.</font>

280
00:18:44,490 --> 00:18:46,846
<font color="yellow">No matter what we tell him right now, he won't listen.</font>

281
00:18:46,871 --> 00:18:48,371
<font color="yellow">So just let it go.</font>

282
00:18:49,451 --> 00:18:50,451
<font color="yellow">Okay?</font>

283
00:18:51,865 --> 00:18:52,865
<font color="yellow">All right.</font>

284
00:18:56,138 --> 00:18:57,684
<font color="yellow">Mom.</font>

285
00:19:11,693 --> 00:19:15,785
<font color="yellow">I can't fall asleep thinking about moving tomorrow.</font>

286
00:19:16,216 --> 00:19:17,216
<font color="yellow">Me, too.</font>

287
00:19:18,841 --> 00:19:21,834
<font color="yellow">Yoo-sung, you need to hurry up and sleep so that we can</font>

288
00:19:21,860 --> 00:19:24,669
<font color="yellow">move tomorrow. If you don't sleep, tomorrow won't come.</font>

289
00:19:25,232 --> 00:19:26,447
<font color="yellow">You're right.</font>

290
00:19:29,255 --> 00:19:30,255
<font color="yellow">Mom.</font>

291
00:19:30,787 --> 00:19:33,966
<font color="yellow">You worked so hard all this time.</font>

292
00:19:37,083 --> 00:19:39,082
<font color="yellow">I didn't do anything.</font>

293
00:19:40,240 --> 00:19:43,560
<font color="yellow">Seung-hee, you were the one who worked hard.</font>

294
00:19:44,998 --> 00:19:50,748
<font color="yellow">Grandma, why do you keep calling aunt "Seung-hee?"</font>

295
00:19:51,310 --> 00:19:54,318
<font color="yellow">Aunt's name is Mi-poong. Kim Mi-poong.</font>

296
00:19:54,857 --> 00:19:56,973
<font color="yellow">Oh, you're right.</font>

297
00:19:57,341 --> 00:19:59,385
<font color="yellow">I forgot.</font>

298
00:19:59,894 --> 00:20:05,194
<font color="yellow">But why do you, my smarty-pants, call your aunt "mommy?"</font>

299
00:20:05,589 --> 00:20:07,346
<font color="yellow">That's because...</font>

300
00:20:07,948 --> 00:20:10,182
<font color="yellow">That's because...</font>

301
00:20:10,425 --> 00:20:15,198
<font color="yellow">Because I fed you milk, carried you on my back, and bathed you.</font>

302
00:20:15,532 --> 00:20:17,761
<font color="yellow">I am your mommy, right?</font>

303
00:20:18,667 --> 00:20:20,617
<font color="yellow">You can call me whatever you want.</font>

304
00:20:21,128 --> 00:20:23,544
<font color="yellow">What will you do if you never get married because of that?</font>

305
00:20:23,737 --> 00:20:24,870
<font color="yellow">What else will I do?</font>

306
00:20:25,275 --> 00:20:30,518
<font color="yellow">I'll keep living with you and Yoo-sung.</font>

307
00:20:34,706 --> 00:20:37,385
<font color="yellow">You really can't fall asleep? Huh?</font>

308
00:20:42,558 --> 00:20:43,558
<font color="yellow">One.</font>

309
00:20:45,660 --> 00:20:46,660
<font color="yellow">Two.</font>

310
00:20:47,965 --> 00:20:48,965
<font color="yellow">One.</font>

311
00:20:49,933 --> 00:20:50,933
<font color="yellow">Exhale.</font>

312
00:20:51,379 --> 00:20:52,379
<font color="yellow">Two.</font>

313
00:20:54,722 --> 00:20:57,222
<font color="yellow">Elder, when you're exercising, breathing is very important.</font>

314
00:20:57,247 --> 00:21:01,778
<font color="yellow">When you lower your arm, you should exhale like this.</font>

315
00:21:02,605 --> 00:21:03,808
<font color="yellow">Yes, just like that.</font>

316
00:21:04,550 --> 00:21:07,831
<font color="yellow">When I pull up my arm, I need to inhale?</font>

317
00:21:07,857 --> 00:21:10,069
<font color="yellow">Okay. Inhale.</font>

318
00:21:11,527 --> 00:21:12,659
<font color="yellow">Exhale.</font>

319
00:21:26,613 --> 00:21:29,308
<font color="yellow">I really hate that song.</font>

320
00:21:29,980 --> 00:21:32,519
<font color="yellow">Who on earth made that kind of song?</font>

321
00:21:33,300 --> 00:21:35,972
<font color="yellow">Why is everyone trying to live until they're a hundred years old?</font>

322
00:21:36,660 --> 00:21:37,660
<font color="yellow">Goodness.</font>

323
00:21:38,612 --> 00:21:39,612
<font color="yellow">I'm so frustrated.</font>

324
00:21:41,478 --> 00:21:47,784
<font color="yellow">"Ask him when I'll naturally be able to go."</font>

325
00:21:48,267 --> 00:21:51,004
<font color="yellow">Is the green vegetable juice not done yet? Elder is thirsty.</font>

326
00:21:51,030 --> 00:21:54,712
<font color="yellow">For how much longer are you going to call him "Elder?"</font>

327
00:21:55,408 --> 00:21:58,897
<font color="yellow">If we decided to serve him as a father, then you should call him father.</font>

328
00:21:59,611 --> 00:22:01,811
<font color="yellow">Is it so hard to call him father?</font>

329
00:22:02,463 --> 00:22:05,732
<font color="yellow">Why are you getting mad at me over nothing so early in the morning?</font>

330
00:22:06,205 --> 00:22:07,821
<font color="yellow">This is "nothing?"</font>

331
00:22:09,010 --> 00:22:14,495
<font color="yellow">You need to call him father so that he'll think of you as his child!</font>

332
00:22:15,369 --> 00:22:17,576
<font color="yellow">Stop talking nonsense and hurry up!</font>

333
00:22:19,908 --> 00:22:21,388
<font color="yellow">Stop turning on that song.</font>

334
00:22:21,861 --> 00:22:23,394
<font color="yellow">I'm getting sick of it.</font>

335
00:22:25,353 --> 00:22:29,820
<font color="yellow">Do you really want father to live until he's a hundred years old?</font>

336
00:22:32,185 --> 00:22:33,185
<font color="yellow">Then?</font>

337
00:22:35,005 --> 00:22:36,005
<font color="yellow">You don't?</font>

338
00:22:36,787 --> 00:22:37,787
<font color="yellow">Well...</font>

339
00:22:38,990 --> 00:22:41,919
<font color="yellow">I just heard it's not good if you live for so long.</font>

340
00:22:43,162 --> 00:22:44,706
<font color="yellow">They say longevity is a disaster.</font>

341
00:22:45,130 --> 00:22:46,542
<font color="yellow">Don't you read the newspaper?</font>

342
00:22:47,583 --> 00:22:52,731
<font color="yellow">You need to live moderately. That's order.</font>

343
00:22:52,757 --> 00:22:54,435
<font color="yellow">Stop talking crap!</font>

344
00:22:56,888 --> 00:22:58,294
<font color="yellow">Crap?</font>

345
00:22:59,802 --> 00:23:02,536
<font color="yellow">Did he just say that I'm talking crap?</font>

346
00:23:14,427 --> 00:23:15,895
<font color="yellow">Elder, you're thirsty, aren't you?</font>

347
00:23:16,310 --> 00:23:17,763
<font color="yellow">Drink this.</font>

348
00:23:18,787 --> 00:23:23,940
<font color="yellow">Today, I mixed enough carrots and apples together, so it won't taste bitter.</font>

349
00:23:24,232 --> 00:23:25,232
<font color="yellow">Is that so?</font>

350
00:23:25,560 --> 00:23:26,560
<font color="yellow">Thank you.</font>

351
00:23:28,185 --> 00:23:29,185
<font color="yellow">Let me try.</font>

352
00:23:33,560 --> 00:23:34,560
<font color="yellow">It's good.</font>

353
00:23:38,662 --> 00:23:43,706
<font color="yellow">Father, how's your condition today?</font>

354
00:23:44,607 --> 00:23:46,941
<font color="yellow">Are you uncomfortable anywhere?</font>

355
00:23:47,365 --> 00:23:52,649
<font color="yellow">I feel great. Thanks to you, I'll be living for a long time.</font>

356
00:23:53,615 --> 00:23:54,615
<font color="yellow">Yes!</font>

357
00:23:56,373 --> 00:23:57,602
<font color="yellow">Of course!</font>

358
00:23:58,044 --> 00:24:01,551
<font color="yellow">You need to live a long life until you're two hundred years old!</font>

359
00:24:01,794 --> 00:24:02,794
<font color="yellow">Two hundred?</font>

360
00:24:05,974 --> 00:24:10,023
<font color="yellow">It's an insult to tell old people to live for a long time.</font>

361
00:24:12,818 --> 00:24:14,552
<font color="yellow">But as for me,</font>

362
00:24:15,091 --> 00:24:17,025
<font color="yellow">I won't ask for more or less.</font>

363
00:24:18,466 --> 00:24:23,731
<font color="yellow">I'm going to live until we're unified and I can step onto my home country.</font>

364
00:24:24,693 --> 00:24:25,999
<font color="yellow">Of course!</font>

365
00:24:26,544 --> 00:24:29,995
<font color="yellow">You need to be healthy until then, so drink up.</font>

366
00:24:30,701 --> 00:24:31,701
<font color="yellow">All right.</font>

367
00:24:32,037 --> 00:24:33,037
<font color="yellow">I'll drink it.</font>

368
00:24:38,849 --> 00:24:41,312
<font color="yellow">Oh, my. So is he saying he'll live over a hundred</font>

369
00:24:41,337 --> 00:24:43,404
<font color="yellow">years old if the countries aren't unified?</font>

370
00:24:45,810 --> 00:24:48,606
<font color="yellow">When on earth will that unification happen?</font>

371
00:25:01,513 --> 00:25:02,513
<font color="yellow">Mom!</font>

372
00:25:04,427 --> 00:25:06,021
<font color="yellow">Did you talk to grandfather about it?</font>

373
00:25:06,169 --> 00:25:07,576
<font color="yellow">Talk to him about what?</font>

374
00:25:08,255 --> 00:25:10,931
<font color="yellow">About buying me a fashion shop in Cheongdam-dong.</font>

375
00:25:11,568 --> 00:25:14,035
<font color="yellow">Cheongdam-dong fashion shop, my foot.</font>

376
00:25:14,998 --> 00:25:18,616
<font color="yellow">I sent you to study abroad, but you didn't even graduate. Shop, my foot!</font>

377
00:25:19,029 --> 00:25:22,476
<font color="yellow">Why do I need to graduate to own a shop? All I need is money!</font>

378
00:25:23,021 --> 00:25:26,787
<font color="yellow">Oh my goodness! Where did you get your stubbornness from?</font>

379
00:25:26,802 --> 00:25:29,816
<font color="yellow">Mom, I'm really confident about it!</font>

380
00:25:30,115 --> 00:25:32,309
<font color="yellow">Although I didn't graduate,</font>

381
00:25:32,334 --> 00:25:35,291
<font color="yellow">but I lived in New York! I have those senses!</font>

382
00:25:35,451 --> 00:25:39,994
<font color="yellow">What's more important for my career than the fact that I was once a New Yorker?</font>

383
00:25:40,302 --> 00:25:43,003
<font color="yellow">You didn't even study. You shopped and played around</font>

384
00:25:43,028 --> 00:25:45,575
<font color="yellow">while spending money. Is that part of your career?</font>

385
00:25:47,223 --> 00:25:51,731
<font color="yellow">I had such a hard time gathering money for your expenses when you were living abroad!</font>

386
00:25:51,919 --> 00:25:53,846
<font color="yellow">Grandfather paid for the tuition.</font>

387
00:25:53,871 --> 00:25:55,817
<font color="yellow">Tuition wasn't the only thing wasted on you!</font>

388
00:25:55,842 --> 00:25:59,004
<font color="yellow">I borrowed money without your dad or grandfather knowing in</font>

389
00:25:59,029 --> 00:26:02,138
<font color="yellow">order to cover up for your costs of living as a New Yorker!</font>

390
00:26:02,740 --> 00:26:05,398
<font color="yellow">That's why I'll pay you back once I make money.</font>

391
00:26:06,005 --> 00:26:08,904
<font color="yellow">Don't even lie.</font>

392
00:26:08,929 --> 00:26:12,412
<font color="yellow">Mom! Shop! Shop! Mom! Shop!</font>

393
00:26:12,437 --> 00:26:15,347
<font color="yellow">What if grandfather finds out you didn't even graduate?</font>

394
00:26:16,036 --> 00:26:19,763
<font color="yellow">If you get on grandfather's bad side, it will be the end of you!</font>

395
00:26:20,310 --> 00:26:23,161
<font color="yellow">If you don't have any brains, the least you should have is some tact!</font>

396
00:26:23,186 --> 00:26:26,090
<font color="yellow">Goodness. Who would know how I feel?</font>

397
00:26:26,833 --> 00:26:30,756
<font color="yellow">No one else will know that I didn't graduate as long as you and Hee-dong stay silent.</font>

398
00:26:31,052 --> 00:26:32,802
<font color="yellow">The two of you are the only ones who know.</font>

399
00:26:33,232 --> 00:26:34,232
<font color="yellow">My gosh!</font>

400
00:26:34,826 --> 00:26:36,988
<font color="yellow">Go and wake up your brother for breakfast!</font>

401
00:26:39,615 --> 00:26:44,824
<font color="yellow">If it hadn't been for Hee-dong, mom wouldn't have found out I hadn't graduated either.</font>

402
00:26:46,552 --> 00:26:47,552
<font color="yellow">Shit!</font>

403
00:26:59,123 --> 00:27:00,123
<font color="yellow">Jo Hee-dong.</font>

404
00:27:04,927 --> 00:27:06,377
<font color="yellow">Jo Hee-dong, you better wake up.</font>

405
00:27:09,203 --> 00:27:11,820
<font color="yellow">How can you act so rudely to your big brother?</font>

406
00:27:11,845 --> 00:27:13,699
<font color="yellow">Brother, my foot.</font>

